<!-- ══════════════════ ESSENTIALS ══════════════════ -->
<section id="essentials">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="reveal">
      <div class="section-label">What to pack</div>
      <h2 class="section-title">Pack these, just in case</h2>
      <p class="section-lead">HCMC is a fully modernised city and you'll find most things you need from home — but a few items are worth bringing with you.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="essentials-grid reveal">
      <div class="essential-item">
        <h4><span>💻</span> Laptop & charger</h4>
        <p>You'll need to bring your own laptop and charger. The centre has adapters and extension leads, so you don't need to bring these for work — but it's handy for personal use.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="essential-item">
        <h4><span>👁</span> Contact lenses</h4>
        <p>Lenses and solution are available in most opticians here, but they are more expensive — worth stocking up before you fly.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="essential-item">
        <h4><span>💄</span> Preferred cosmetics</h4>
        <p>Larger department stores do stock cosmetics, but it's not guaranteed your personal favourites will be available. Bring your essentials.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="essential-item">
        <h4><span>👟</span> Large shoes (size 10+)</h4>
        <p>Shoes are easy to find in HCMC, but if you're over a UK size 10 (male) or 5 (female), pack a couple of extra pairs. Sports trainers in premium brands also come at a premium here.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="essential-item">
        <h4><span>☀️</span> Suncream</h4>
        <p>The sun will be shining as soon as you step off the plane. Many Asian creams contain whiteners, so bring your preferred brand to start with.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="essential-item">
        <h4><span>🩱</span> Swimwear (larger sizes)</h4>
        <p>Finding comfortable underwear (size 14+) and swimwear (size 12+) can be challenging. Larger department stores have more variety but can still be difficult.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="essential-item">
        <h4><span>🩺</span> Medication (3 months)</h4>
        <p>If you take any prescription medication, bring at least a three-month supply. You'll generally be able to find alternatives, but if your medication is specialised, bring more.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="essential-item">
        <h4><span>🍵</span> Tea (optional)</h4>
        <p>Vietnam is a tea-drinking nation, but if you're a Yorkshire or PG Tips loyalist, pack a box. International supermarkets do stock UK brands, but they come at a premium.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="essential-item">
        <h4><span>👗</span> Smart clothing</h4>
        <p>All ITG staff must dress smartly. Please review the ITG Staff Dress Code for what you'll need for your first day. You'll find plenty of good options here once you arrive.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

